SUMMARY:Deadline: Rooted Futures Lab: Environmental Justice & Technology (E
 JIT) Fellowship - Summer 2026
DESCRIPTION:Project-based summer fellowship for individuals working at the 
 intersection of technology\, infrastructure and environmental justice. Eac
 h Fellow contributes to a defined project area working independently and i
 n close collaboration with Rooted Futures Lab staff and other Fellows. All
  tracks produce tangible outputs that support communities\, advance critic
 al inquiry and strengthen the broader EJIT field. Summer 2026 tracks: (1) 
 Data Centers & Environmental Justice: Creative Technologist Fellow\; (2) D
 ata Centers & Environmental Justice: Investigative Storyteller Fellow\; (3
 ) Study Hall: Democratic Governance & Collective Systems Fellow\; (4) GLIT
 CH Zine: Editor & Strategist Fellow. Applications reviewed on a rolling ba
 sis\; status notification within 3 weeks of the deadline. Inclusive select
 ion: RFL does not discriminate on sexual orientation\, gender\, gender ide
 ntity\, race\, ethnicity\, religion\, age or economic background\, and exp
 licitly encourages applicants from underrepresented identities. Inspired b
 y Dr. Robert Bullard's environmental justice framework and Octavia Butler'
 s histofuturism. Questions: info@rootedfutureslab.io (subject 'EJIT Fellow
 ship Application').\n\nOrganisation: Rooted Futures Lab\nLocation: Remote 
 (worldwide)\nAward: $3\,000 USD stipend (flexible payment schedule)\nDurat
 ion: ~12 weeks (15 June to 4 September 2026)\, ~20 hours/week (flexible)\n
 \nMore: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdXR7TbhqyY65XKH4M0gxlV-C
 ZunuEdKW0R1fOuSydHNxn71A/viewform
URL:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdXR7TbhqyY65XKH4M0gxlV-CZunuE
 dKW0R1fOuSydHNxn71A/viewform
LOCATION:Remote (worldwide)
END:VEVENT
